### Breakpoints

| Prefix | Min Width | Target |
|--------|-----------|--------|
| (none) | 0px | Mobile (default) |
| `sm:` | 640px | Large phones |
| `md:` | 768px | Tablets |
| `lg:` | 1024px | Laptops |
| `xl:` | 1280px | Desktops |

### Correct

```tsx
<div className="text-sm md:text-base lg:text-lg">
  Mobile-first sizing
</div>

<div className="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4">
  Stack on mobile, row on tablet+
</div>

<div className="px-4 md:px-6 lg:px-8">
  Progressive padding
</div>
```

### Forbidden

```tsx
<div className="text-lg sm:text-base xs:text-sm">
  Desktop-first (hard to maintain)
</div>

<div className="hidden sm:block md:hidden lg:block">
  Inconsistent visibility toggles
</div>
```

## Accessibility

Ensure all interactive elements have proper focus states and sufficient contrast.

### Rules

1. **Focus states** - All interactive elements must have visible focus indicators
2. **Color contrast** - Minimum 4.5:1 ratio for text
3. **Touch targets** - Minimum 44x44px for clickable elements
4. **Screen reader** - Use `sr-only` for visually hidden but accessible text

### Correct

```tsx
<button className="focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:ring-offset-2">
  Accessible button
</button>

<a className="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 underline">
  Accessible link
</a>

<input className="focus:border-blue-500 focus:ring-1 focus:ring-blue-500" />

<span className="sr-only">Loading...</span>
<div aria-hidden="true" className="animate-spin" />
```

### Forbidden

```tsx
<button className="focus:outline-none">
  No focus indicator
</button>

<p className="text-gray-400">
  Low contrast text on white background
</p>

<button className="w-6 h-6">
  Too small touch target
</button>
```

## Spacing Consistency

Use Tailwind's spacing scale. Reserve arbitrary values for design-specific requirements only.

### Spacing Scale

| Class | Value | Use For |
|-------|-------|---------|
| `1` | 4px | Tight gaps |
| `2` | 8px | Small gaps |
| `4` | 16px | Default spacing |
| `6` | 24px | Section gaps |
| `8` | 32px | Large gaps |

### Correct

```tsx
<div className="p-4 mb-6 gap-4">
  Consistent scale
</div>

<div className="space-y-4">
  Uniform vertical spacing
</div>

<div className="mt-8 pt-8 border-t">
  Section divider
</div>
```

### Forbidden

```tsx
<div className="p-[13px] mb-[22px] gap-[7px]">
  Random arbitrary values
</div>

<div className="mt-3 mb-5 pt-7">
  Inconsistent spacing
</div>
```

### Rules

1. **Use scale values** - `p-4`, `gap-6`, `mb-8`
2. **Arbitrary only when required** - For exact design specs like `h-[42px]`
3. **Be consistent** - Same spacing for similar elements
4. **Use `space-y/x`** - For uniform child spacing
